{
  "texts": [
    "Section 2 illustrates how PAC-Bayes bounds can be applied to such estimators.",
    "Moreover, many non-randomized estimators can be derived from randomized ones: aggregation rules, majority vote classifiers, etc.",
    "The PAC-Bayes bounds on the randomized estimator often brings strong information on the de-randomized version.",
    "This will also be discussed thoroughly and illustrated in Section 2.",
    "• Bayesian estimators incorporate prior knowledge through a prior distribution π on Θ."
  ]
}